  "agreement_with_libirrep_ed": "All four sector ground states match libirrep_sg_heisenberg_sector_build_at_k to 8+ digits. The sector-projecting Lanczos defeats the machine-precision leak amplification that previously caused un-projected Lanczos to return the global B_1 ground state from any sector seed.",
  "notes": "First demonstration that sector-resolved low-energy spectra can be obtained from random NQS-seeded Lanczos via in-loop projection. The seed quality (training) doesn't matter for this small cluster — the projection step does. At larger N where full Lanczos is no longer free, the same projector applied during a sparse-matvec Lanczos becomes the load-bearing infrastructure for sector-restricted variational ED."
